She's all this and more because she is our school nurse and she is a Springfield superhero. Happy School Nurse's Week to our very own Mrs. Ricciani!

post_text: 4th grade students, Mason Delanos,Izabella Kinney, Isabella Kokotajlo, Gabriella Pollack, & Ruby Rincon were selected to participate in the 2020 All-South Jersey Elementary Chorus Festival on Saturday, March 7th at Washington Township High school in Washington Township, New Jersey. Over 30 schools in South Jersey sent their top singers to participate in the event. The students had to learn and memorize seven pieces, from a variety of music genres in only a few weeks. The students did an outstanding job representing Springfield School! Huge shout out to Mrs. Weir for her support & guidance!

Over 30 schools in South Jersey sent their top singers to participate in the event. The students had to learn and memorize seven pieces, from a variety of music genres in only a few weeks. post_text:
Well we did it...another amazing holiday season at Springfield Elementary School. Our elf Holly will have so many great things to report to Santa next week! A big thank you to our H&S for a December filled with a Santa breakfast, holiday shop, & today's class parties. Shout out to our incredible faculty & staff for their continued hard work for our students and a special word of gratitude to our school nurse for facilitating our holiday gift drive....what a difference our school community makes. Our custodial & maintenance crew put in some long days keeping our school safe & clean, so they're definitely on the nice list! And a jumbo stocking sized thank you to the Board of Education for supporting everything we do to make not only December, but every month (even July & August), rich and rewarding for our students at Springfield Elementary.

Wishing all of our Springfield families a safe & happy holiday....can't wait to see all of the amazing things 2020 will bring for our spectacular little school.

We are Springfield. That means something.

post_text: Due to the anticipated black ice and dangerous road conditions, we will have a 90 minute delayed opening on Thursday, February 8, 2018. During a 90 minute delay, our student hours are 10:20 to 3:20 (parent drop off begins at 10:00). Lunch will be served; however the cafeteria will not be serving breakfast. Please be sure to visit the school website for additional schedule details (including preschool hours).

post_text: Our Springfield crew showed their Eagles spirit today! Other schools might have spent their week going over the top (ahem district that rhymes with Spoutspamton), but at Springfield we choose to keep our focus on learning rather than decorating (cue video of mic drop). We reserved a little bit of today though to get fired up for the Super Bowl....and our students brought the heat as usual! Special thanks to our Spirit Squad for snapping all the great pictures and handing out some prizes! No need to be flashy when your school is as awesome as ours!

post_text: Due to the potentially hazardous road conditions, Springfield Elementary School will have a 90-minute delayed opening on Tuesday, January 9, 2018. School will open at 10:20 (student drop off begins at 10:00) with normal dismissal time for K-6 students. The 3-year-old preschool program will run from 10:30 to 12:15 and the 4-year-old program will run from 1:15 to 3:00.
text: Due to the potentially hazardous road conditions, Springfield Elementary School will have a 90-minute delayed opening on Tuesday, January 9, 2018. School will open at 10:20 (student drop off begins at 10:00) with normal dismissal time for K-6 students. The 3-year-old preschool program will run from 10:30 to 12:15 and the 4-year-old program will run from 1:15 to 3:00.

post_text: Due to the expected unsafe road conditions and dangerous temperatures, Springfield Elementary School will be closed on Friday, January 5, 2018. Details regarding make-up days for the school closings will be provided via email soon. Be safe and enjoy the extended weekend.

We are hosting a special community seminar regarding the safe and responsible use of digital media on Thursday, January 11, 2018. All parents and community members are invited to attend this presentation, which will be held from 6:30 to 8:00PM in our school cafeteria. Additionally, we will be providing childcare for any school-aged children (ages 5 & up only). Please register to attend via the link below:
